article.headline: Cleveland St. 67, Kent St. 41
article.story: CLEVELAND -- J'Nathan Bullock had 24 points and 10 rebounds to lead Cleveland State to a 67-41 victory over Kent State on Tuesday night. Cleveland State (9-4) allowed Kent just 17 points in the first half as the Golden Flashes shot 24 percent from the field. Cedric Jackson added 11 points for Cleveland State, and Norris Cole had 10. Chris Singletary led Kent State (5-6) with 13 points, and Tyree Evans had 12. Kent stayed close early until the Vikings took the lead for good on a layup by Cole that made it 11-9 after nearly 8 minutes. From there, it was all Cleveland State, which led 32-17 at the half and by at least 21 for the final 17:46 after a dunk by Bullock.
